With the appearance of a strange daruma doll, ordinary life crumbles away in an instant. Even so, live on. Survive. This is the story of the "life" bestowed upon all those who have wished to die. description: Ever since a horde of seemingly immortal and mindless giants emerged a century ago, humanity has been eking out a secluded existence behind a series of concentric walls. The precarious peace does not last, and childhood friends Eren, Armin, and Mikasa, who witness the end of the world as they know it, embark on an infernal journey with no paradise in sight. In this novelization of both parts of the mega-hit comic’s theatrical adaptation, the series’ familiar setting, plot, and themes are reconfigured into a compact whole that is fully accessible to the uninitiated and strangely clarifying for fans of the original.
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Attack on Titan: End of the World

"COPPELION", a special unit of the third division of Japan's Ground SelfDefense Forces made up of three high school girls, genetically engineered to be impervious to radioactivity, is sent in to Tokyo; "The City of Death".

description:
Still not fully healed from the wound of breaking up with Tsukushi and the shock of seeing Nobuta again, Serizawa starts an internship at a law firm. Through a mix-up over the phone, he becomes acquainted with a certain someone—a woman who otherwise wouldn’t be in his reach! Will this chance encounter start Serizawa on the path to his first truly adult relationship?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 30: Nobuta 3
  • Chapter 31: Kim Sam-soon 1
  • Chapter 32: Kim Sam-soon 2
  • Chapter 33: Kim Sam-soon 3
  • Chapter 34: Kim Sam-soon 4

description:
New meetings always come suddenly! The protagonist, Yuu Haruna, moves into a new town where he meets a somewhat strange girl who doesn't have a cell phone. The girl, Fuuka, seems to have a strange allure that draws people to her, very much like a summer breeze. Looks like Yuu has been caught up in one wild love story!

  • Chapter #96: Clash!
  • Chapter #97: Day Two!
  • Chapter #98: Collaboration!
  • Chapter #99: Our Wings!
  • Chapter #100: The Best Night!
  • Chapter #101: Precious Song!
  • Chapter #102: The Hopes Handed Down.
  • Chapter #103: Just Maybe.
  • Chapter #104: 365 Days.
  • Chapter #105: The Truth Revealed.

description:
He Can Run, But He Cannot Hide...

After Sena unexpectedly told Kodaka how she felt about him, he ran awake...and a week later, he still hasn't been back to the Neighbors Club. Instead, he's been forging new connections--with the girls from the student council!

But Kodaka can't hide from his complicated club relationships forever, especially when things aren't going so well with the Neighbors Club in his absence. And if he won't come back on his own, Rika's ready to take things into her own hands...!
name: Vol. 14

volume.name: Haganai: I Don't Have Many Friends

description:
A mysterious beauty who bumps into Shuusuke in passing, then winds up holding onto the package he drops!

A mysterious beauty seated next to Nao, who becomes separated from her friends when classes change!

Hikawa Hozumi is this mysterious beauty, who somehow manages to meet and befriend both of the Takanashi siblings independently. Will this new player bring new challenges to Shuusuke and Nao's relationship?!
name: Vol. 9-10

volume.name: I Don't Like You At All, Big Brother!!

description:
Both touched by spirits called yokai, Kotoko and Kuro have gained unique superhuman powers. But to gain her powers Kotoko has given up an eye and a leg, and Kuro’s personal life is in shambles. So when Kotoko suggests they team up to deal with renegades from the spirit world, Kuro doesn’t have many other choices, but Kotoko might just have a few ulterior motives …

Note: The digital edition (11/22/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Vol. 1

description:
When exorcist Hiyakawa and his assistant, Mikado, discover the remains of a curse at a murder scene, the only clue they have to the caster’s identity is the name “Erika Hiura.” Later, while investigating an incident at a girls’ school, they finally come face-to-face with their mysterious quarry. Although Hiyakawa is stunned to find that Erika is just a high-school student, he’s even more disturbed by the instant, powerful attraction felt between Erika and Mikado—a bond he’s determined to break, at any cost.

Chapter 7 - 12 and Treasure Hunt bonus story.
name: Volume 2

volume.name: The Night Beyond the Tricornered Window

description:
Erika Hiura leads a strange double life as both a normal high school student and a secretly powerful necromancer whose services are sold to the highest bidder. Her interest in exorcist odd couple Hiyakawa and Mikado seems innocent, but when they’re called in to investigate a missing-persons case, the connections between the three may be deeper than any of them realize. Meanwhile, the relationship between Hiyakawa and Mikado continues to evolve in ever more intimate, and disturbing, directions.

Chapter 13 - 18 and Mikado's Mesmerizing Body bonus story.
name: Volume 3

volume.name: The Night Beyond the Tricornered Window

description: Superstar teen idol Rise Kujikawa escapes to Inaba for a much-needed break from the limelight, and the usually sleepy town is caught in the grip of celebrity fever! But when Rise suddenly appears on the Midnight Channel and goes missing soon thereafter, it's up to Soji, Chie, and the rest of the crew to rescue her from the TV World and figure out what - if anything - Rise shares in common with the previous kidnapping victims. Based on the popular Persona 4 video game!
name: Vol. 4

description: With Rise rescued and now in possession of her own Persona, Soji and friends welcome a powerful new ally into the fold. But just as things are looking up, the body of Inaba's latest murder victim is discovered - and the victim's identity turns our heroes' investigation upside-down. Meanwhile, Teddie does some much-needed soul searching... and what he finds is much more than anyone bear-gained for!
name: Vol. 5

description:
Please Tell Me! Galko-chan is a comedy manga series, presented as unforgettable all-color comic strips about the chatty and lovable Galko-chan giving advice to her high school friends.

Galko-chan always speaks her mind, which may not be the wisest decision in all cases, but it’s never short of entertaining! Meet the exuberant and unbelievably busty high schooler, Galko, as she traverses the ups and downs of adolescence with spirit and verve, alongside her best friends--the anti-social loner, Otako, and the unpredictably honest, Ojyo.
name: Vol. 1
